00:50:45.460 --> 00:50:49.549
You know, they
know how to do this kind of propaganda.

00:50:49.549 --> 00:50:51.900
But our side
doesn't pick up.

00:50:51.900 --> 00:50:53.270
My side.

00:50:53.270 --> 00:50:57.079
And so, I have to say we got
one far right party and we got one center

00:50:57.079 --> 00:50:58.589
right party.

00:50:58.589 --> 00:51:01.650
And we've got the rest of America scratching
their heads

00:51:01.650 --> 00:51:05.060
saying, "we don't like Washington, because
nobody's

00:51:05.060 --> 00:51:07.109
representing us."

00:51:07.109 --> 00:51:13.450
And that to my mind is the biggest
problem that -- you know, one side is really,

00:51:13.450 --> 00:51:16.010
as I said
and I think you feel it the same way from

00:51:16.010 --> 00:51:20.980
a moral point of
view -- completely un-understandable from

00:51:20.980 --> 00:51:28.970
the perspective
of the most -- just modicum of decency, compassion,

00:51:28.970 --> 00:51:32.390
basic
standards of values -- but the other side

00:51:32.390 --> 00:51:33.390
is dishonest.

00:51:33.390 --> 00:51:37.310
&gt;&gt;Male #1: If what you're saying is right,
I spent most of my

00:51:37.310 --> 00:51:42.160
youth growing up overseas -- places like Ethiopia
during

00:51:42.160 --> 00:51:48.089
revolutions, in Berlin when the Russians were
-- when the

00:51:48.089 --> 00:51:51.000
government becomes that disconnected from
the people.

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:54.571
&gt;&gt; Jeffrey: And it's the right and the duty
of the people to

00:51:54.571 --> 00:51:55.849
overturn it I think is the expression.

00:51:55.849 --> 00:52:01.390
&gt;&gt; Male #1: There is only one thing that happens.

00:52:01.390 --> 00:52:03.880
That is not
just people sitting in the park.

00:52:03.880 --> 00:52:05.339
That is violence.

00:52:05.339 --> 00:52:06.920
How
do we avoid that?

00:52:06.920 --> 00:52:13.790
&gt;&gt; Jeffrey: My belief is that we've had -- I
hope we do.

00:52:13.790 --> 00:52:18.950
I think
that the path that we're on is incredibly

00:52:18.950 --> 00:52:21.560
dangerous.

00:52:21.560 --> 00:52:24.660
And
I think the way we avoid it most likely is

00:52:24.660 --> 00:52:30.259
to come
together around a set of proposals -- a platform

00:52:30.259 --> 00:52:34.760
-- and
elect candidates that are going to carry that

00:52:34.760 --> 00:52:36.030
out.

00:52:36.030 --> 00:52:38.799
Our
structural problem is our politics on both

00:52:38.799 --> 00:52:41.000
sides are on
the take.

00:52:41.000 --> 00:52:47.040
And so, they're not offering the median
voter -- answer their happily duopoly on the

00:52:47.040 --> 00:52:51.700
right of
keeping taxes low and slashing the rest of

00:52:51.700 --> 00:52:52.920
government.

00:52:52.920 --> 00:52:56.400
And that's kind of a safe comfortable incumbent
duopoly

00:52:56.400 --> 00:52:59.870
that's not capturing the center.

00:52:59.870 --> 00:53:04.089
I think a good
political entrepreneur who's clever could

00:53:04.089 --> 00:53:10.390
capture the
center and capture power or political movement

00:53:10.390 --> 00:53:11.750
could do
so.

00:53:11.750 --> 00:53:16.220
The trick is big money can't do that and won't
do

00:53:16.220 --> 00:53:17.240
that.

00:53:17.240 --> 00:53:20.790
So my view, structurally, is that the solution
is,

00:53:20.790 --> 00:53:27.299
"How do you run and win power without campaign
contributions?"

00:53:27.299 --> 00:53:31.599
That to my mind is the real structural
challenge.

00:53:31.599 --> 00:53:34.920
And my view is that it's possible these days.

00:53:34.920 --> 00:53:38.030
If everyone's got their Androids.

00:53:38.030 --> 00:53:39.160
If everyone's
tweeting.

00:53:39.160 --> 00:53:46.000
If everyone is using YouTube and Facebook
and

00:53:46.000 --> 00:53:49.740
every social network -- what we ought to do
is create a

00:53:49.740 --> 00:53:55.200
platform that is the free campaign platform
-- the whole

00:53:55.200 --> 00:53:57.290
social media platform.

00:53:57.290 --> 00:54:04.330
You have a message, we'll retweet
it a million times in a day.

00:54:04.330 --> 00:54:07.170
We'll make sure that videos
go viral.

00:54:07.170 --> 00:54:11.599
We'll use Facebook network that's created
of a

00:54:11.599 --> 00:54:16.540
nationwide friends of progressive ideas.

00:54:16.540 --> 00:54:21.380
And enable
candidates to run without being on the take.

00:54:21.380 --> 00:54:24.840
So that's
the revolution in campaign tactics that I

00:54:24.840 --> 00:54:27.670
think could be
the breakthrough.

00:54:27.670 --> 00:54:33.380
And then, if the platform is right,
then I think the rest can follow.

00:54:33.380 --> 00:54:36.370
That's my strategy.

00:54:36.370 --> 00:54:38.160
What do you think?

00:54:38.160 --> 00:54:39.160
You ready?

00:54:39.160 --> 00:54:41.549
&gt;&gt; Male #1: The Internet will set you free?

00:54:41.549 --> 00:54:42.690
[laughter]
&gt;&gt; Jeffrey: Yes.

00:54:42.690 --> 00:54:43.710
What do you think, guys?

00:54:43.710 --> 00:54:44.710
You're Google.

00:54:44.710 --> 00:54:45.710
[Applause].

00:54:45.710 --> 00:54:47.349
&gt;&gt; Jeffrey: All right.

00:54:47.349 --> 00:54:50.930
Can you guys make the right platform?

00:54:50.930 --> 00:54:53.710
Google dot democracy.org?

00:54:53.710 --> 00:54:56.720
All right.

00:54:56.720 --> 00:54:59.380
We may tax you a
little bit more in the meantime also, but.

00:54:59.380 --> 00:55:01.569
&gt;&gt; Male #2: Jeffrey, thank you for being here.

